pageContext.claim: “So -- and they have. They've been working on [the Women's Suffrage Centennial Coin Act] for years and years. And I'm curious, why wasn't it done a long time ago, and also -- well, I guess the answer to that is because now I'm President, and we get things done.”
pageContext.analysis: Women earned the right to vote in 1920. It makes sense that the coin celebrating its 100th anniversary would pass 100 years later. It has nothing to do with Trump’s presidency.
